a:2:{s:7:"content";s:925:"<h4>Essential Question</h4>
<p>How can we build a visual intuition for algebraic representation?</p>
<h4>Overview</h4>
<p><a href="https://bhi61nm2cr3mkdgk1dtaov18-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Border-Problem-final-copy.pdf">The Border Problem</a> is a classic from <a href="https://www.youcubed.org/">YouCubed</a>, and one of my favorite ways to start a unit on algebra because it promotes rich dialogue, creates a need for students to devise new tools and methods of representation, and is a great activity for setting norms in the classroom. Students are shown this image for only a few seconds, and then challenged to determine how many red squares there are.<br />
